<br>
I’m not offering this as an excuse.  I wish we weren’t this way.  But it is a truism that people feel differently about what’s truly important  when things are going well then they do when they are faced with a challenge.<br>
<br>
The same thing happens on so many levels.  Think of two brothers.  They might fight all the time and beat the heck out of each other regurlarly, but let someone else step in and attack one of them, then they forget their differences and stick up for each other.<br>
<br>
What would be truly tragic is if something as terrible as what happened on 9/11 and the people in CA didn’t react as if it was their brother who was attacked.  That would make me cry.<br>
