<br>
The IOC has bowed to pressure, and as a comprimise the WTC flag will be presented seperately from the parade of nations by a delegation composed of firefighters, policemen and other groups associated with the events of 9/11.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, this still doesn't address what could have been a display of world unity because only Americans will be involved in this presentation.  I say unfortunate because the olympics are the only event where the world could actually perform a physical symbol of their loss together, and the unity that loss has generated.<br>
<br>
I guess I should be happy that Americans are going to present that flag, but I'm not.  More than Americans died that day.  With this compromise, it seems to belittle their deaths.<br>
